        public Valve(@NotNull
             @NotNull Valve valve)
        Copy constructor. This is a shallow copy, i.e., If the field value is a reference to an object (e.g., a memory address) it copies the reference. If it is necessary for the object to be completely independent of the original you must ensure that you replace the reference to the contained objects. You must replace node1 and node2 to do the copy independent of the original
